-- IMF, World Bank Hold Talks With Guinea Over Resuming Operations, RTG Says
-- B y   O u g n a   C a m a r a
-- 2010-12-20T11:41:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/imf-world-bank-hold-talks-with-guinea-over-resuming-operations-rtg-says.html
The World Bank and the International
Monetary Fund have begun talks with  Guinea  on restarting
operations in the West African nation, state-owned Radio
Television Guineenne reported.  The lenders met Prime Minister  Jean Marie Dore  and are
expecting more discussions in January, the Conakry-based
broadcaster cited World Bank Country Director Ishac Diwan as
saying.  International donors, including the bank and the fund, cut
 development funding  following the December 2008 military coup
that took place following the death of the long-time President
 Lansana Conte .  Alpha Conde  is expected to be sworn in as
president in the capital tomorrow, after he won an election Nov.
7 that marked the countryâ€™s return to civilian-led rule.  To contact the reporter on this story:
